{"questionId":"22168497","questionHtml":"<p>Find the equation of a third parallel plane <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Π</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> which is also a perpendicular distance of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>11</mn></msqrt></math> from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Π</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Valid method to find a point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> on <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Π</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>AC</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mover><mi>BA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>BC</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mover><mi>BA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> as the midpoint of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BC</mi></math>.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mover><mi>OC</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mover><mi>OC</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfen